                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/10610</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-08T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6206. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 425. Embassy’s No. 5638, October 30, 9 p.m., your 549. Because of delay
                    involved, we are unable to concur in resolution of Paris conference. All members
                    of Washington conference agree that action of the conference should become
                    effective immediately. <persName>Frothingham</persName> notified as
                    requested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
